{
  "texts": [
    "Given x ′ R i y ′, we may go up in the first coordinate to any x above x ′ to obtain xR i y ′.",
    "A solid arrow from s to t indicates that t is a refinement of s (t ⊑ s), while a dashed arrow indicates that t is accessible from s (sR i t).x yy ′ ⇒ x y y ′ Figure 2.2: the R-down condition from Example 2.7.",
    "Given xR i y, we may go down in the second coordinate to any y ′ below y to obtain xR i y ′.The logic of intuitionistic modal frames is the logic HK introduced in § 1.1.Theorem 2.8 (Božić and Došen 1984).",
    "HK is sound with respect to the class of all intuitionistic modal frames and complete with respect to the class of full intuitionistic modal frames.",
    "Our third example of partial-state frames will be quite important for our purposes."
  ]
}